  "prompt": "Why was MM kalburgi killed?",
  "response": "M.M. Kalburgi, a prominent Indian scholar, rationalist, and academic known for his critical views on religious orthodoxy and superstition, was assassinated on August 30, 2015. Kalburgi's outspoken nature and criticism of idol worship and other religious practices made him a target for extremist groups. His murder is believed to be connected to his progressive and rationalist stance, which provoked backlash from conservative and fundamentalist factions that opposed his opinions on religion and cultural practices. The investigation into his death suggested that his assassination was part of a broader pattern of violence against intellectuals and activists who challenge orthodox beliefs in India.",
